PUPILS at the M.C. Weiler Primary in Alexandra made a shocking discovery of a human skeleton under one of the mobile classrooms at the school. The Gauteng Department of Education confirmed the discovery of what is alleged to be a human body underneath a mobile classroom within school premises on Thursday, 2 June 2022. This unsettling discovery was made during the school break between 11h00 and 11h30 when learners allegedly went to fetch a soccer ball that was underneath the Grade 5A mobile classroom. In a statement, Gauteng Education spokesman Steve Mabona said the learners reportedly identified their discovery as a human skeleton and immediately informed their educators. He said subsequently, the school’s management contacted the police and released learners at 13h00 to allow police officials to conduct necessary investigations. "Police officials inspected the scene and the learner’s discovery was confirmed to be a human skeleton. " Mabona said. "The body was then removed from the scene and police indicated that an inquest case will be investigated accordingly," he added. The Gauteng Department of Education has dispatched its Psycho-Social Unit at the school to provide counseling and trauma support for all affected learners and Staff. “While we await further reports from the police regarding this matter, learning at the school will continue with necessary psycho-social support. " Gauteng education MEC Panyaza Lesufi said.